    Classes in de.unisb.cs.st.javaslicer.common.classRepresentation.instructions that implement Instruction
    Modifier and Type Class Description
    class  AbstractInstruction
    Abstract superclass that builds the basis for most Instruction implementing classes.
    class  ArrayInstruction
    Class representing an array load or array store (*ALOAD / *ASTORE) instruction.
    class  FieldInstruction
    Class representing a field instruction (GETFIELD, PUTFIELD, GETSTATIC or PUTSTATIC).
    class  IIncInstruction
    Class representing an IINC instruction.
    class  IntPush
    Class representing an instruction that just pushes an integer onto the stack (except ICONST_*, so just BIPUSH and SIPUSH).
    class  JumpInstruction
    Class representing a conditional or unconditional jump instructions (one of IFEQ, IFNE, IFLT, IFGE, IFGT, IFLE, IF_ICMPEQ, IF_ICMPNE, IF_ICMPLT, IF_ICMPGE, IF_ICMPGT, IF_ICMPLE, IF_ACMPEQ, IF_ACMPNE, GOTO, JSR, IFNULL and IFNONNULL).
    class  LabelMarker
    This is no read instruction, but a marker for jump targets.
    class  LdcInstruction
    Class representing an LDC instruction.
    class  LookupSwitchInstruction
    Class representing a LOOKUPSWITCH instruction.
    class  MethodInvocationInstruction
    Class representing a method invokation instruction (INVOKEVIRTUAL, INVOKESPECIAL, INVOKESTATIC or INVOKEINTERFACE).
    class  MultiANewArrayInstruction
    Class representing a MULTIANEWARRAY instruction.
    class  NewArrayInstruction
    Class representing a NEWARRAY instruction.
    class  SimpleInstruction
    Class representing an instruction with no arguments.
    class  TableSwitchInstruction
    Class representing a TABLESWITCH instruction.
    class  TypeInstruction
    Class representing an instruction that takes a type as argument (NEW, ANEWARRAY, CHECKCAST, INSTANCEOF).
    class  VarInstruction
    Class representing a local variable instruction (one of *LOAD, *STORE, RET).
